reason.tex:
%text All differential equations are not solved in the same way.
The most efficient way to solve a differential depends on the \underline\text{type of equation}
For the types you will encounter, the texhniques are summarized below.
% \begin{tabular}{|c|c|} \hline \text{Type} & \text{First Step} \\ \hline \frac{dy}{dx} = g(x)\cdot h(y) & \frac{dy}{h(y)} = g(x)\cdot dx \\ & \therefore \int\frac{dy}{h(y)} = \int g(x)\cdot dx \\ \hline \frac{dy}{dx} = g\left(\frac{y}{x}\right) & \text{Let }y = v\cdot x \\ & \therefore \frac{dy}{dx} = v + x\frac{dv}{dx} = g(v)\\ \hline \frac{dy}{dx} + Px = Q & \text{Find the integrating factor} \\ & j(x) = e^{\int P\cdot dx} \\ & \text{Multiply both sides with $j(x)$} \\ \hline \end{tabular}
